@node BAR_CONSTRUCTOR "bar_plugin: Constructor"

   @{BG shine}Constructor@{BG back}

      @{b}bar(@{"tags" link BAR_TAGS}=NIL:PTR TO tagitem)@{ub}

      For creating a new plugin object use for example:
      @{FG fill}
      DEF bar:PTR TO bar_plugin
      NEW bar.bar([..., TAG_DONE])
      @{FG text}

@endnode

@node BAR_METHODS "bar_plugin: New Methods"

   @{b}set(@{"tag" link bar_TAGS}, value)@{ub}

      By calling this method it's possible to change attributes
      at runtime. You can use all tags with the S flag set.
      This method can also be used before the GUI is created and when
      the window is closed.
      Value is a LONG and contains the argument for the used tag.
      @{FG fill}
      Example:
      DEF bar:PTR TO bar_plugin
      ...
      NEW bar.bar([..., TAG_DONE])
      ...
      bar.set(PLA_Bar_Disabled, TRUE)
      ...
      @{FG text}


@endnode

@node BAR_TAGS "bar_plugin: Tags"

 The letters [IS.] show you when the tags can be used.
 I = @{"Initalisation" link BAR_CONSTRUCTOR}
 S = @{"Set Method" link BAR_METHODS}


    @{FG shine}PLA_Bar_Percent@{FG text}            [IS.]

        How much of the allocates space the actual rendering
        of the bar should fill up (this number should be
        between 1 and 100).


    @{FG shine}PLA_Bar_Vertical@{FG text}           [I..]

        Boolean; if FALSE (default), the bar will be
        horizontal, if TRUE then it will be vertical.


@endnode

